## Key learnings
- CCE range checks MUST use numeric positions, never char-code-at on boundary chars
- CCE encodes lowercase by frequency (e=13, t=14, a=15), not alphabetically
- Char literal escape values must be CCE codes, not Unicode codepoints
- Record fields in Codex literals must be in DEFINITION order (compiler bug: source order used for positional constructor)
- Bootstrap1 batch pipeline doesn't use module markers (uses C# ModuleScoper)
- Bare-metal pipeline uses dump-source which has markers
